	<div class="ibox-image"><a href="./File:Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg" src="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/2e/Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg/300px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg" decoding="async" width="300" height="300" srcset="https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/2e/Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg/450px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg 1.5x, https://resources.allsetlearning.com/gramwiki/images/thumb/2/2e/Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg/600px-Chinese-grammar-wiki-zhe.jpg 2x" /></a></div>
</div>
<p>Expressing something's existence in a certain place or location is not just limited to 在 (zài) and 有 (yǒu). The word order may be a little different from what you are used to, but 着 (zhe) and 是 (shì) are also ways to make everyday statements such as, "There is a book lying on the desk."
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="Alternative_existential_sentences#Pattern_with_.E7.9D.80"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Pattern with 着</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="Alternative_existential_sentences#Structure"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="Alternative_existential_sentences#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="Alternative_existential_sentences#Pattern_with_.E6.98.AF"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Pattern with 是</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="Alternative_existential_sentences#Structure_2"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
